“落日余晖医生”，还珍藏了另一张照片。
"Doctor Sunset Yuhui", but also the collection of another picture.
黄祺。
Wangqi.
新民周刊                      。
Xinmin Weekly.
新民周刊。
Xinmin Weekly.
深度和角度——这就是我们能做的。
Depth and angle - that's what we can do.
。
.
她说：我相信你们一定是一群最美丽的人，等疫情过去，我要对着小本本认一认，我要带着每一位好好看看武汉的美景。
I believe you must be a group of the most beautiful people, after the epidemic, I would like to look at the small book, I will take everyone to see a good look at Wuhan.
文｜黄　祺昨天从隔离病房下班拿到自己的手机，复旦大学附属中山医院援鄂医疗队队员刘凯医生被“吓一跳”，他的照片不仅朋友圈刷屏，还有好多未接的记者来电等着他。
Wen Huang Qi yesterday got his cell phone from the isolation ward, and Dr. Liu Kai, a member of the Hubei Medical Team attached to Fudan University's Zhongshan Hospital, was "startled".
武汉疫情一个多月后，太多人期待重见阳光，而这张患者和医生一起看夕阳的照片，照亮了人们阴霾多日的心。
Wuhan epidemic more than a month later, too many people look forward to seeing the sun again, and this patient and the doctor together to see the sunset, lit up people's cloudy heart for many days.
照片最早刊登于复旦大学附属中山医院的官方微博，说明描述：照片拍摄于武汉大学人民医院东院，中山医院援鄂医疗队队员刘凯医生在护送病人做CT途中，停下来，让已住院近一个月的87岁老先生欣赏了一次久违的日落……接受《新民周刊》采访时刘凯医生表示，看到照片刷屏，惊讶也惊喜。
The photos were taken at the East Hospital of the People's Hospital of Wuhan University. Dr. Liu Kai, a member of the Hubei Medical Team, escorted the patient to a CT scan and allowed the 87-year-old, who had been in hospital for nearly a month, to see a long sunset.
“很高兴大家喜欢这张照片，不过我希望大家不用太多关注我个人，千万医生和我一样在这里战斗，很多人来得比我更早，比我更辛苦。
"I'm glad you like this picture, but I hope you don't have to pay a lot of attention to me personally. Thousands of doctors fight here like me.
”刘凯医生是2月7日抵达武汉的中山医院援鄂医疗队队员，医疗队一百多名医护人员由资深专家和年轻骨干组成，到武汉后承担了重症患者的救治重任。
"Dr. Liu Kai arrived in Wuhan on February 7 to help medical teams from the Zhongshan Hospital in Hubei, where more than 100 medical personnel, composed of senior experts and young cadres, took on the heavy responsibility of treating patients with serious illnesses.
刘凯医生告诉《新民周刊》，中山医院第四批援鄂医疗队，整建制接手武汉大学人民医院东院区两个重症病房，医疗队队长是罗哲教授。
Dr. Liu told Xinmin Weekly that the fourth medical team from Zhongshan Hospital in Hubei province had taken over two intensive care units in the East Campus of Wuhan University.
“我们收治的都是重症患者，经过近一个月的治疗，患者大多数平稳或转轻，有部分已经治愈出院了，但还是有小部分病情危重，不过我们相信疫情最严重的阶段很快就要结束了。
"We are treating very serious patients, and after nearly a month of treatment, most of the patients are stable or light, some of them have been cured and discharged, but a small number of them are in serious condition, but we believe the worst phase of the epidemic will soon be over.
”2月7日出发时，右一为刘凯医生关于照片背后的故事，刘凯医生介绍，病床上的老人过去是乐团小提琴手，身体状况好的时候喜欢唱唱歌。
"When he left on February 7, the story behind the photo was on the right of Dr. Liu Kai, who said the man in the hospital bed used to be a violinist and loved to sing when he was in good health.
上海医疗队刚接手时，老人病情非常严重，不与人交流，拒接家人的电话。
When the Shanghai medical team first took over, the old man was very ill, did not communicate with people, refused to receive family phone calls.
老人家住得比较远，家人送生活用品不方便，医护人员就承担起照料老人生活的任务。
The old people live far away, the family members send the daily necessities inconvenient, the medical personnel take care of the elderly people's life.
最近几天，老人病情好转，需要做CT检查看看恢复的情况。
In recent days, the elderly are getting better and need a CT scan to see if they can recover.
做完检查回病房的路上，正是夕阳余晖满天，“我就问老人家要不要停下来看看太阳，老人说，好。
On the way back to the ward, the sun was setting. "I asked the old man if he wanted to stop and look at the sun.
” 这一幕被一位志愿者用手机记录下来。
The scene was recorded by a volunteer on a cell phone.
27岁的刘凯医生，自我评价性格“有时比较粗，做事比较细，还经常比较逗比”。
The 27-year-old Dr. Liu Kai, self-assessment character "sometimes coarse, do more detailed, often more teasing."
这一次变“网红”让他措手不及。
This time the "net red" caught him off guard.
刘凯医生的岗位，准确说叫“呼吸治疗师”，这个新的职业名称刚刚出现在3月2日人力资源和社会保障部等国家多部门联合发布的16个新职业名单中。
Dr. Liu Kai's job, better known as "respiratory therapist," has just been added to a list of 16 new jobs released on March 2 by national departments such as the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security.
重症监护室是刘凯的主战场，下面这张照片，是刘凯的同事偷拍到的。
Liu Kai's intensive care unit is the main battlefield, the following photo, Liu Kai's colleagues snapped.
记录了平常工作中，刘凯监护一名ECMO治疗病人，睡眠太少，在监护室外席地睡着的一幕。
Liu Kai records the usual work, Liu Kai custody of an ECMO treatment patients, sleep too little, in the monitor on the floor of the scene.
其实，刘凯医生还珍藏了另一张照片。
In fact, Dr. Liu Kai also treasures another picture.
这是一位病人在纸上写下的救治和照顾过她的所有医护人员的名字，刘凯医生的名字也在其中。
It was the name of all the paramedics a patient wrote on paper to treat and care for her, and Dr. Liu Kai's name was included.
照片是中山医院援鄂医疗队党支部副书记潘文彦护士长拍的。
Photographed by Head Nurse Pan Wenyan, Deputy Secretary of the Hubei Medical Team of Zhongshan Hospital.
潘文彦告诉《新民周刊》，写名字的病人，之前非常悲观，几乎不跟任何人说话。
Pan told Xinmin Weekly that the patients who wrote their names had been so pessimistic that they hardly spoke to anyone.
经过了解，患者年迈的母亲因新冠肺炎刚刚去世，她的爱人也在其他医院治疗。
After understanding that the patient's elderly mother died of pneumonia, her wife was also treated in other hospitals.
她沉浸在绝望的情绪中，根本无心治疗。
She was in such a state of despair that she had no care at all.
潘文彦说，中山医院援鄂医疗队达成共识，不仅要战胜病魔，更要帮助患者战胜“心魔”。
Pan said that the medical team in Zhongshan Hospital reached consensus not only to defeat the disease, but also to help the patient overcome the "heart demon."
“每天进入病房，大家都会问候她。
"Everyone greeted her when they entered the ward every day.
我们温柔的一句‘阿姨，您今天好吗’，会给她很大的鼓励。
Our gentle words, 'Aunt, how are you today', will give her a lot of encouragement.
我们鼓励她做肺康复，帮助她生活护理，让她重拾信心和勇气。
We encouraged her to do lung rehabilitation, to help her life care, to restore her confidence and courage.
时间久了，她慢慢愿意和我们医护人员说话了，她会问：‘你们是哪里来的？’”潘文彦发现，这位病人总爱在自己的小本子上写啊写。
As time went on, she was slowly willing to talk to our paramedics, and she would ask, 'Where did you come from?' Pan found that the patient always wrote and wrote on his own little book.
有一天进病房时，患者拿出了小本本，潘文彦看到了上面这张写满名字的纸。
One day when entering the ward, the patient took out a small book, and Pan saw the name-filled paper on it.
患者对潘文彦说：“护士长，我指标好转了，很快就能出院了，我现在特别想记住你们的样子，但你们都穿着防护服，每个人看起来都是一样的，所以我在自己的本子上，记下了每一位治疗护理我的医护人员防护服后的姓名。
The patient told Pan, "Nurse, I'm getting better and will be out of the hospital very soon. I want to remember what you look like, but you're all wearing protective clothing and everyone looks the same, so I wrote down the names of each of my paramedics in my book.
”她说：我相信你们一定是一群最美丽的人，等疫情过去，我要对着小本本认一认，我要带着每一位好好看看武汉的美景。
"I believe you must be the most beautiful people in the world," she said. "When the outbreak is over, I will recognize the book and take everyone with me to see the beautiful scenery of Wuhan.
征集令阳春三月，万物复苏。
Call for Spring March, all things revive.
在抗击疫情的战斗中，我们迎来了春天，《新民周刊》也迎来了新闻线索和故事征集的第二弹。
In the fight against the epidemic, we ushered in the spring, "New People's Weekly" also ushered in the news clues and the second round of story collection.
如今，经历了一个多月休眠的城市正在逐渐苏醒，各行各业都开始有序复工复产。
Now, after more than a month of dormancy of the city is gradually waking up, all walks of life began to orderly resumption of work.
不论您是企业老板、管理者，还是普通员工；又或者，您是老师、家长，还是学生本人……我们希望了解复工复产复学过程中的困难，或暖心故事。
Whether you're a business owner, a manager, or an employee, or whether you're a teacher, parent, or student... we'd like to know about the difficulties of getting back to work, or a warm heart story.
如果你是抗疫一线的医生护士，疫情期间拍下了珍贵的摄影作品，也欢迎联系我们投稿。
If you are a first-line doctor and nurse against the epidemic, you have taken valuable photographs during the epidemic and are welcome to contact us for contributions.
当然，抗击新冠肺炎疫情的相关故事，我们仍然欢迎。
Of course, the story of fighting the outbreak of New Crown Pneumonia is still welcome.
希望广大读者朋友，提供相关线索，说出你的故事，让我们用新闻留存这一切。
I hope that the general reader friends, provide relevant clues, tell your story, let us use the news to retain all this.
